<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="763" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/333.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am authorized by the President of Honduras to state that he will not
                            again submit to Congress the loan convention now pending in the United
                            States Senate, even if ratified by that body, considering the rejection
                            by the Congress of Honduras as final. He is however disposed to make a
                            loan convention, since a large loan is necessary but cannot be made
                            except under such a guaranty.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">White.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>